                    You can click on the image below to find my **GitHub** account and all the projects I'm working on.

            p.am-center
                a.am-image-link(href='/code', title='My account on GitHub')
                    img.am-image-hub(src='/img/hub.png', alt='')

        article.am-article.am-bio
            a(name='bio')
            section.am-section
                :markdown
                    I live in [Buenos Aires, Argentina](http://goo.gl/maps/beVu1 "Google Maps"). I started programming in [Pascal](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pascal_(programming_language)) in the late 90’s.

                    [BASIC](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BASIC "BASIC Programming Language") came shortly afterwards on the [TI-74](http://i.imgur.com/CLLvJqN.jpg "Texas Instruments 74 BASICALC") my dad gave me, and, with it came [VB6](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Visual_Basic "Visual Basic"). Soon after that I discovered an [open-source C# game server](http://www.runuo.com/ "RunUO MMORPG server"), and I was **stoked**.

                    I started building all kinds of web applications using **C#**, and developed a great interest in **JavaScript**, UX and, well, _front-end in general_. I’ve now shifted my focus towards [Node](http://nodejs.org "NodeJS platform"). Late in 2012, I [started](http://blog.ponyfoo.com/2012/12/25/pony-foo-begins "Pony Foo Begins") coding this blogging platform, where I maintain [my own blog](/blog "Browse My Blog").

                    I also [read](http://blog.ponyfoo.com/2013/05/21/recommended-reading "My Recommended Reading"). _A lot_.

                    Below is a link to _detailed information about my career_, gently hosted by Stack Overflow, [where I also have an account](/stackoverflow).

            p.am-center
                a.am-image-link(href='/career', title='My career on Stack Overflow')
                    img.am-image-hub(src='/img/me.jpg', alt='')
